UPDATE AND VIDEO: People are asking: You said it was one of the most haunted places… so what else happened?? We wish we could’ve shown two hours of this case! We investigated the entire second building (Sybil’s home) including the massive General Store on the first floor. There was a disembodied male voice during one of the camera interviews that stopped everyone in their tracks, we played cards with a ghost on the third floor, we heard footsteps on the third floor, back at the museum we got activity in the doll room, and when we put the Doctors bag in a different room to see if that would help we heard a very sad female moan coming down the hall from that room as if to let us know they were NOT ok with the bag being in their space. Maybe we can do a special one day and show all the extra clips and talk about all the things you didn’t see! 

FOR NOW: Here is a clip of us visiting the Fox Sisters property during the case. Another thing we didn’t have time to show you. This was incredibly special for us and something we will never forget.

location.city_name: Princess Cruise Lines Departing Seattle To Alaska

social_posts.post_text: Welp. When you couldn’t think this trip could get any more exciting… your parent surprise you on the boat!! I mean they got us!!! We saw their names show up on the app as part of our circle. We’ve cruised together before and this happens when you follow someone on the app. But we had no idea and it wasn’t really confirmed until we saw them. I called my brother and he is a VERY good secret keeper! Haha. Such a great surprise!

First day of the @strangeescapes Alaskan cruise. We left Seattle with a little bon voyage party but not before my parents surprised on by showing up on the trip. Incredibly excited and they pulled it off!! Haha we had no idea. Then we really wanted to take a photo despite the wind… So. Damn. Funny.

Happy Father’s Day to @aguyberryjr!! I was gonna post an old photo, something that showed a memory. A sentimental moment. Yet why bother when you can get a current picture of memories being made in real time!! Love you Dad and thank you for being so fantastic. One of a kind and always up for a good time. Here’s to many more adventure. #Rampitup #RollTide #SurpriseCruise #Alaska

Yesterday was epic! First up: helicopter flight to a glacier to a dog sledding camp. We learned all about the dogs, camp, and got to learn how to mush! Our lead dog “mama” subbed in for another dog during the Iditarod and did the last 600 miles! She was incredible. #Alaska

These past two months have been so insane! To say that they were uneventful would be the biggest lie of the century! Stating June with an epic @strangeescapes at @belvoirwinery. Followed by @thebennyberry and I closing on our first home. To sailing the seas with another Escape to Alaska and back with friends, family, and an incredible group. Two different theater talks for @ghoststoriesonstage. Producing and opening @peregrinetheatre’s first production, since the pandemic halted our creative energy, to critic and audience acclaim. Recording my audio book for Goodbye Hello. Beginning the pre-production for a new work with Peregrine. Capped off with our first house guest visit, with aunt Wanda. I am beyond grateful and oh so thankful for these extraordinary experiences and  lifelong memories. I am also tired. 🤣 As we head into August, I plan to take more time to pause and enjoy the last big month of summer. Staring off with seeing Beyoncé tomorrow night! Family visits, workshops, and Michigan Paracon to come!

FIRST REVIEW AND PRAISE for my new book! “The book brings together interviews with psychic mediums, religious scholars, and ordinary people who have connected with the spirits of loved ones, as well as his own personal stories and learnings.
